-- models/intermediate/int_deduped_billing_events.sql
-- Deduplicate billing_events to one row per subscription + event_month
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        subscription_id,
        event_month,
        amount,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY subscription_id, event_month
            ORDER BY event_id DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_billing_events') }}
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

```sql
-- models/intermediate/int_subscriptions_enriched.sql
-- Enrich subscriptions with user and company info, handle missing plans
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        s.subscription_id,
        s.user_id,
        s.plan_id,
        s.started_at,
        s.ended_at,
        s.status,
        u.company_id,
        COALESCE(p.tier, '(unknown)') AS tier,
        COALESCE(c.industry, '(unknown)') AS industry
    FROM {{ ref('stg_subscriptions') }} s
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_users') }} u
        ON u.user_id = s.user_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_plans') }} p
        ON p.plan_id = s.plan_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_companies') }} c
        ON c.company_id = u.company_id
)
SELECT * FROM source
```

-- models/intermediate/int_monthly_active_subscriptions.sql
-- Determine which subscriptions are active each month
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        DATE_TRUNC('month', be.event_month)::DATE AS event_month,
        se.subscription_id,
        se.user_id,
        se.tier,
        se.industry
    FROM {{ ref('int_deduped_billing_events') }} be
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_subscriptions_enriched') }} se
        ON se.subscription_id = be.subscription_id
)
SELECT * FROM source
```

```sql
-- models/marts/fct_monthly_subscription_metrics.sql
-- Monthly subscription metrics: active subscriptions, MRR, unique users by tier and industry
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        mas.event_month AS month,
        mas.tier,
        mas.industry,
        COUNT(DISTINCT mas.subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
        SUM(be.amount) AS total_mrr,
        COUNT(DISTINCT mas.user_id) AS unique_users
    FROM {{ ref('int_monthly_active_subscriptions') }} mas
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_billing_events') }} be
        ON be.subscription_id = mas.subscription_id
        AND DATE_TRUNC('month', be.event_month)::DATE = mas.event_month
    GROUP BY
        mas.event_month,
        mas.tier,
        mas.industry
)
SELECT * FROM source
